-- Hungary Stocks: Mol, Magyar Telekom Shares Move in Budapest
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-05-09T15:43:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-09/hungary-stocks-otp-bank-fhb-shares-move-in-budapest-trading.html
Hungary ’s benchmark  BUX (BUX)  index fell 1.7
percent to 17,223.53 by the close in Budapest, the biggest
decline since April 23.  The following were among the most active shares in the
Hungarian market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Mol Nyrt. (MOL)  , Hungary’s largest refiner, dropped 2.1
percent to 16,500 forint after the government said energy
companies will have a 30 percent total tax burden from next
year.  Magyar Telekom Nyrt. (MTELEKOM HB), the Hungarian unit of
Deutsche Telekom AG, fell 3.3 percent to 466 forint. The
government today approved a new levy on telephone calls.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
